# StockRight — Cursor Rules

## TypeScript
- Strict mode always. No `any`, no `as any`, no `@ts-ignore` without a comment explaining why.
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` for error handling; narrow with type guards before use.
- Use `satisfies` for type-safe object literals where applicable.

## Colors & Design Tokens
- NEVER hardcode hex colors, rgb values, or named colors in source code.
- Web: always use `var(--token-name)` or Tailwind classes mapped to tokens.
- Mobile: always use `tokens.*` imported from `@stockright/shared/tokens`.
- Brand amber text must be `--brand-text` (#8C4A12). NEVER use `--brand-ui` (#C8712A) for text.
- Violation example (BAD): `color: "#C8712A"` or `style={{ backgroundColor: "orange" }}`

## Input Font Size
- Input `font-size` MUST be 16px (web: `text-[16px]`, mobile: `fontSize: 16`).
- This is LOCKED. Smaller font causes iOS to auto-zoom the viewport on focus. Never change it.

## Touch Targets
- All interactive elements MUST have a minimum touch target of 48px height.
- Visual height can be smaller (e.g., 36px) but the touchable area must pad to 48px.

## Layout / Responsive (web only)
- BottomTabBar appears ONLY on `<640px`. SideNav appears ONLY on `≥640px`. Never both simultaneously.
- Mobile-web (`<640px` web): no separate top header; wordmark lives in SideNav on desktop only. Account/offline strip is desktop-only (`≥640px`) above page content.
- Desktop web: primary tab CTAs sit in the page title row (right-aligned), not in a global top bar.
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) — no custom CSS media queries.

## Loading States
- Use skeleton screens (shimmer animation) for all loading states.
- NEVER use bare spinners as the primary loading indicator for page-level content.
- **Buttons:** show a **loading label** (e.g. Sending…, Verifying…) via `loadingLabel` / label swap — never a spinner **inside** the button (brand spec §3.5).

## UI Copy Rules (from brand spec §7)
- NEVER use: "sync", "transaction", "SKU", "inventory", "ERP", "module", "portal"
- PREFER: "receive" over "inward", "dispatch" over "outward" in user-facing copy
  (Note: use inward/outward as code/token names, but human-readable labels say receive/dispatch)
- No jargon. Write as if explaining to a first-time warehouse owner.

## Font Family
- Web: Noto Sans (UI text), Noto Serif (display headings), Noto Sans Mono (numbers/quantities)
- Mobile: `NotoSans-Regular`, `NotoSans-Medium`, `NotoSans-SemiBold`, `NotoSerif-Regular`, `NotoSerif-SemiBold`
- NEVER substitute Latin-only fonts (Lora, Playfair Display, Inter) — they break Telugu script.
- Always include subsets: `["latin", "telugu", "devanagari"]` in next/font configs.

## Golden Rule
- Any feature added to web MUST be simultaneously added to mobile, or deferred with a tracked issue.
- Any feature added to mobile MUST be simultaneously added to web, or deferred with a tracked issue.
- Shared logic (validation, API calls, types) MUST live in `packages/shared`, not duplicated.

## Security
- Never log OTP codes, session tokens, or user PII.
- Always validate user input with Zod at system boundaries.
- Edge Functions must verify JWT before any privileged operation (`verify_jwt = true` in config.toml).

## Comments
- Write comments only when the WHY is non-obvious.
- No docblock comments (JSDoc/TSDoc) unless generating a public library API.
- No "added for X feature" or "used by Y component" comments — they rot.
